    "## 8. Log-Likelihood and NFXP\n",
    "\n",
    "**Log-likelihood:**\n",
    "$$\\ell(\\theta) = \\sum_{i,t} \\log P(y_{it} \\mid \\ell_{it}, d_{it}, e_{it}; \\theta)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**NFXP (Rust 1987):** outer bounded L-BFGS-B minimizes $-\\ell(\\theta)$; inner VFI solves the Bellman equation at each candidate $\\theta$. The six-parameter estimator is used below as a diagnostic before imposing the switching-cost normalization.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Parameter vector:**\n",
    "$$\\theta = [\\alpha_2,\\; \\gamma,\\; \\beta^{sc}_{12},\\; \\beta^{sc}_{21},\\; \\beta^{dep}_1,\\; \\beta^{dep}_2]$$"
   ]
